column2: Cloudy- calm- slight. sprinkle- low 60's F.
Clear and the water is smooth.
Partly cloudy and a slight west wind- a beautiful day.
Cloudy- some seeds floating on the surface.
Partly cloudy  Water level: up a couple inches
Beautiful- partly cloudy- and two loons.
INSIDE FILTER PAPER FOLDED WITH ALGAE ON OUTSIDE NOT ON INSIDE
Slight wind- cool- sunny- beaver are back after 40 years.
Partly cloudy- slight chop on the lake.
Partly cloudy- windy- sheltered at sample location- loon family putting on a show- baby is ten days old today
Partly cloudy- baby loon seems to be close today
Beautiful blue sky- slight wind- fish are jumping all around me.  The ducks and I own the lake.  Frost the last two nights.
Hot.  Partly cloudy- loon lost their baby this year.  Wood duck houses successful.  Three different houses with young.  One hen lost 6 out of 12 the first night they hatched- 31 degrees that night.
Partly cloudy- hot weather has created more algae.
Five inches of rain in the past 2 weeks.
Water level is high- not as clear as usual- quiet and partly cloudy.
Foggy. Drizzling.  A.M. temperature is 60 degrees F.
Light breeze and 80 degrees. Beautiful day. Loons observed
Cool breezy clear and 58 degrees.  No loons.
Cool and breezy. Partly cloudy and 55 degrees. No loons.
Overcast- a lot of suspended particles in the water.
Clear morning- 58 F- wind NW 10-15 mph- one loon- some popple cotton on the water.
Overcast morning- few showers- temp 48 F- wind ENE about 10 mph- one loon observed- water not as clear as usual.
Partly cloudy. Largest amount of suspended particles I've seen in 17 years.
Clear morning.  Wind light wnw.  One loon + one mature eagle observed.  Some bloom in water.
Overcast- 58 F- some sun peeking through- light SW breeze- storm later- 2 loons observed but no chick.
Clear.  Wind NW 10 mph.  Temp 50 F.  Past peak color.  Fishing has been good.  Loons gone.
Clear sky- pair of loons on lake.
Foggy- warming- 60 deg. F- wind calm- water very warm for this early- loons disturbed from nesting site- chemicals arrived late- old chemicals wouldn't precipitate- couldn't do D.O. test
Pair of loons with 2 chicks- partly cloudy.
Clouds breaking up- wind light and variable- 2 loons observed with 2 new babies- worried about them-temp-62 deg. F- will be near 80 deg. later- new chemicals arrived.
Clear- pair of loons with 2 chicks.
Clear day- beautiful 65 deg. F- west breeze 5-10 mph- lake level down in spite of a wet summer- lake not as clear as usual- 2 baby loons with parents-growing fast- doing well.
Clear- all 4 loons still on lake.
Overcast- fog is lifting- 62 deg. F- southeast breeze 5-10 mph- lake still down somewhat- loons still here-young are as big as parents- some color in maples
Cloudy- cool 43 deg. F- light wind- leaves are pretty well down- lots of leaves in water- water clearer than earlier- some grouse activity- deer laying low.
Cloudy- cool (50 deg F). W wind 10-15 mph. 1.25" rain yesterday. Swallows all over skimming across water. Saw eagle yesterday. Loons are back and nesting on island.
Overcast- 50 deg F. Light east breeze. Has been cloudy- cool- and rainy for the last 2.5 weeks. Fishing has slowed. Loons still nesting. Rain expected later.
Partly cloudy- 60 deg F. Light west wind- 5-10 mph. Nice morning with rain in forecast for PM. No loon chicks this year- done nesting. Fishing slowing down.
Cloudy- warm and humid- a few showers. Heat index for today forecast at 105. Wind from SW at 10 mph. No loons this morning. It's too warm in the woods.
Beautiful fall day. Sunny- warm (70 deg F) with a W wind about 10 mph. Color at or near peak. Loons gone. Fishing has been slow. Forecast is rain tonight- cool later this week.
Cloudy- cool- temperature near 50. Wind calm with occasional breeze from west.Very little green showing in the treetops. Countryside littered with down branches.
Hazy sunshine- temperature 68 F. Wind calm- trees pretty well leafed out.Popple cotton about gone. Loon on her nest. Bluegills still on beds. Seeing fawns.
Partly cloudy- temp 80 degrees. Northwest wind 10-15 mph. Thunderstorms in AM. 1/2" rain. Three adult loons observed. No chicks. Weather has been hot and humid.
Mostly cloudy- lake level up a couple inches from rain

column1: the last two weeks.  Still a couple inches low.

column2: Partly cloudy- 68 degrees. Northeast wind at 5-10 mph. One loon observed. Rusty crab population down. Weeds seen to be coming back. Alone on lake today.
Sunny- humid- temperature about 65 F. Light west breeze. Color starting to come. One young loon observed. Attracted to boat- not afraid. Seems late to have loons.
Pair of loons on the lake- partly cloudy
Sunny- pair of loons on the lake
Clear- breezy. Temperature in the low 50s. Trees beginning to green out.  Bass starting on the beds. One loon observed. Fishing has only been fair.
Thin overcast- sun peeking out.  Wind from E about 5 mph.  Trees pretty well leafed out. Some popple cotton on the water. No loons observed.
Overcast- breezy- wind southeast at about 15 mph. Temperature 65 F. No loons observed. Rainstorms last night- and a cold front moved through.
Overcast. Light breeze from the west.  Weather has been cloudy- rainy and cool for this time of year.  Two loons observed.
Nice fall day. Supposedly the start of a warming trend.  Some color- but nowwhere near peak as yet. Temperature about 50 F. Wind west about 10 mph. Water very clear. Grous hard to find.

Partly cloudy- cool 50 F- Westerly breeze 5-10 mph.  2 loons on lake.  Tree tops just starting to green up.  Temperature was 20 F this morning.  Fishing good over the weekend.  Chemicals bad - no D.O. reading possible.
Overcast day.  Loon sitting on its nest.
Partly cloudy- humid.  Temperature about 70 F.  High expected in mid 80s.  2 loons observed but no nesting activity.  Some popple cotton on water.  Water very clear.  New equipment used.
Partly cloudy- hazy sunshine.  Wind W at 10-15 mph.  Rain forecast for tomorrow.  Temp. 70 F.  3 loons observed- all adults.  Lake is clear.  Weed growth up.  Not many rusty crabs let.
Partly cloudy- 72 F.  Wind SW at about 10-15 mph.  Rain forecast for tomorrow.  All year- temperature top to bottom more or less constant.  Oxygen all over.  One loon seen.
Partly cloudy- 50 F.  Wind calm to light from the East.  Leaves pretty well down.  Has been cool.  Bass biting but not walleyes.  Grouse hunting should improve with better vision.
Mostly cloudy and windy.  Lake up 3" from 2 weeks ago.
2 loons on the lake.  Popple fuzz covering the lake.
Clear sky- one loon on the lake
1 loon on the lake.  Mostly cloudy.
Mostly cloudy.  Two loons on the lake.
Two adult loons with 2 young on the lake
Clear skys- slight chop/waves on the lake
Two young loons still on the lake.
Lake was lower earlier but came back up 6".

column1: Two adult loons with a pair of chicks

column2: Mostly cloudy. One adult and two young loons on tne lake.
Partly cloudy. Two adult and two young loons on the lake.

column1: One adult loon and one young loon on the lake.

Cloudy- Taking the boat off the lake today.
Partly cloudy- 3 adult loons on the lake
more weed in lake than before and more algae
1 lot of 5"-6" large mouth and small mouth bass
Partly cloudy- one loon on nest and one on lake
Partly cloudy- 2 loons on the lake and a bald eagle flew over.
Could not get on lake in May
Mostly cloudy- 3 loons on the lake
Mostly sunny- 5 loons on the lake
Overcast- 5" of rain in the past two days. Two loons on the lake.
Mostly cloudy- saw a loon and osprey
Mostly cloudy- saw a loon and eagle
Partly cloudy- 2 loons on the lake
Partly cloudy- 2 loons on the lake
Clear sky- one loon on the lake
Partly cloudy- 1 loon and 1 eagle seen.
